{{nihongo|Shujukoku|侏儒国|しゅじゅこく}} is a country of [[Dwarf (mythology)|dwarves]] thought to be located south of [[Yamatai]]koku, which appears in [[History of China|Ancient China]]'s [[Book of the Later Han]] and [[Records of the Three Kingdoms]]. In [[Records of the Three Kingdoms|Wei Zhi]]. It is mentioned together with [[Black tooth country]] and Naked country.

== Overview ==
The following are listed in Chinese history books. [[Book of the Later Han]] and the so-called [[Wajinden|Wajin Biography]] in [[Records of the Three Kingdoms]] state that it is located 4,000 miles south of the queen state of [[Wakoku|Wa-koku]].

The [[Classic of Mountains and Seas|Shanhai Jing]], a document that precedes the [[Wajinden]], mentions an island called {{ill|Shojin|lt=Shojin-koku|ja|小人_(中国の伝説)|12=draft|12=draft}} in the eastern sea. The same book also mentions other dwarfs such as "{{Nihongo|2=焦僥}}", "{{Nihongo|2=周饒}}", and "{{Nihongo|2=菌人}}" living in the east and south. The words "{{Nihongo|2=焦僥}}" and "{{Nihongo|2=周饒}}" have the same pronunciation and etymology as {{Nihongo|2=侏儒}}, which is originally the same word.

== Wajinden ==
According to the [[Wajinden]]{{Quote frame|There is also a dwarf country in the south of it, the people are three or four feet long, to the queen more than 4,000 miles.}}

== [[Book of the Later Han]] ==
According to the [[Book of the Later Han]]{{Quote frame|More than 4,000 miles south of the Queen's country to Zhu Ru country, people are three or four feet long. From Zhu Ru southeast ship for a year, to the naked country, the black tooth country, so that the post transmission, the extreme is here.}}

==  Main comparative sites  ==

=== Tanegashima ===
{{Main|Tanegashima}}
Many have identified [[Tanegashima]] with Shujukoku.<ref name="邪馬台国-石原洋三郎-令和元年10月-第一印刷p18-2">邪馬台国　[[石原洋三郎]]　令和元年10月　第一印刷P18-p23。</ref>。This is the result of a study of human bones excavated from Tanegashima Island from the Yayoi period to the Kofun period, with "extreme" short head, short head, and short stature characteristics<ref>種子島における古人骨形質の時代変化　竹中正巳　2009th year 。</ref> and that it is consistent with the anthropological characteristics of Shujukoku described in the [[wajinden]].
{{Citation needed span|This feature is not found in Okinawa, Kyushu, or Honshu, where human remains from the same period have been discovered, and "dwarf-like" adult human remains are found only on Tanegashima Island.|date=June 2022}}This is the reason why [[Tanegashima|Tanegashima Island]] is located in the south of Kyushu.
[[Tanegashima]] is located about 4,000 ri south of northern Kyushu, which is about 4,000 ri in the shortest sense of the word, so some [[Yamatai Kyushu Theory|Yamatai Kyushu Theorists]] have compared the country to Tanegashima.<ref name="邪馬台国-石原洋三郎-令和元年10月-第一印刷p18-2" />。

