The [[:en:Classic of Mountains and Seas|Shanhai Jing]], a document that precedes the [[Wajinden]], mentions an island called {{ill|Shojin|lt=Shojin-koku|ja|小人_(中国の伝説)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shojin|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} in the eastern sea. The same book also mentions other dwarfs such as "{{Nihongo|2=焦僥}}", "{{Nihongo|2=周饒}}", and "{{Nihongo|2=菌人}}" living in the east and south. The words "{{Nihongo|2=焦僥}}" and "{{Nihongo|2=周饒}}" have the same pronunciation and etymology as {{Nihongo|2=侏儒}}, which is originally the same word.
== Wajinden == According to the [[Wajinden]]{{Quote frame|There is also a dwarf country in the south of it, the people are three or four feet long, to the queen more than 4,000 miles.}}
== [[:en:Book of the Later Han|Book of the Later Han]] == According to the [[:en:Book of the Later Han|Book of the Later Han]]{{Quote frame|More than 4,000 miles south of the Queen's country to Zhu Ru country, people are three or four feet long. From Zhu Ru southeast ship for a year, to the naked country, the black tooth country, so that the post transmission, the extreme is here.}}
== Main comparative sites ==
=== Tanegashima === {{Main|Tanegashima}} Many have identified [[Tanegashima]] with Shujukoku.<ref name="邪馬台国-石原洋三郎-令和元年10月-第一印刷p18-2">邪馬台国 [[石原洋三郎]] 令和元年10月 第一印刷P18-p23。</ref>。This is the result of a study of human bones excavated from Tanegashima Island from the Yayoi period to the Kofun period, with "extreme" short head, short head, and short stature characteristics<ref>種子島における古人骨形質の時代変化 竹中正巳 2009th year 。</ref> and that it is consistent with the anthropological characteristics of Shujukoku described in the [[wajinden]]. {{Citation needed span|This feature is not found in Okinawa, Kyushu, or Honshu, where human remains from the same period have been discovered, and "dwarf-like" adult human remains are found only on Tanegashima Island.|date=June 2022}}This is the reason why [[Tanegashima|Tanegashima Island]] is located in the south of Kyushu. [[Tanegashima]] is located about 4,000 ri south of northern Kyushu, which is about 4,000 ri in the shortest sense of the word, so some [[Yamatai Kyushu Theory|Yamatai Kyushu Theorists]] have compared the country to Tanegashima.<ref name="邪馬台国-石原洋三郎-令和元年10月-第一印刷p18-2" />。
